'''Adarsh Liberal''' (an Ideal Liberal) is a sarcastic term used on social media in [[India]] to describe a person who blindly opposes the policies of the Modi Government. The term came to be used on social media after the term ''Bhakt'' became popular to describe a person who blindly supports the policies of the [[Modi Government]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/blogs-trending-31833682 |title=Indian liberals mocked - and mocking - online - BBC News |publisher=Bbc.com |date=2015-03-11 |accessdate=2015-08-09}}</ref>
According to a poster released on social media, ''Adarsh Liberal'' is "someone who goes on an expensive holiday to discuss and understand poverty", and a person who "supports [[People for the Ethical Treatment of Animals|PETA]] but eats chicken and beef", "shifts goalposts if losing arguments", "questions Hindu mythology to become secular" etc.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/adarshliberal-or-adarshbhakt-adarsh-liberal-cartoon-ignites-hashtag-war-on-twitter/article1-1325203.aspx |title=Adarsh Liberal vs Adarsh Bhakt: Hashtag war on Twitter |publisher=Hindustantimes.com |date= |accessdate=2015-08-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ndtv.com/offbeat/viral-memes-a-war-between-adarsh-liberal-and-adarsh-bhakt-on-twitter-745783 |title=Viral Memes: A War Between 'Adarsh Liberal' and 'Adarsh Bhakt' on Twitter |publisher=Ndtv.com |date= |accessdate=2015-08-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibnlive.com/news/buzz/adarsh-liberal-vs-adarsh-sanghi-the-battle-of-ideologies-on-twitter-972620.html |title=Adarsh Liberal vs Adarsh Sanghi: The battle of ideologies on Twitter |publisher=IBNLive |date= |accessdate=2015-08-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abplive.in/india/2015/07/30/article668096.ece/An-open-letter-by-a-thulla-to-all-those-opposing-Yakub-Memons-capital-punishment |title=ABP Live - English News, Today’s Latest Breaking News in English, Online English News |publisher=Abplive.in |date=2015-07-30 |accessdate=2015-08-09}}</ref> It is a minor alteration of the old term ''Adarsh Balak'' which is used to make fun of [[Liberalism in India|Indian liberals]].{{Self-published inline|certain=yes|date=December 2017}}<ref>{{cite web|author=Shovon Chowdhury |url=http://scroll.in/article/717655/is-scroll-in-a-nest-of-adarsh-liberals |title=Is Scroll.in a nest of Adarsh Liberals? |publisher=Scroll.in |date= |accessdate=2015-08-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fakingnews.firstpost.com/2015/08/pakistan-apologizes-to-adarsh-liberals-for-deterioration-in-quality-of-terrorists/ |title=Pakistan apologizes to Adarsh Liberals for deterioration in quality of terrorists &#124; Faking News |publisher=Fakingnews.firstpost.com |date= |accessdate=2015-08-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.reshareit.com/18-tweets-by-adarsh-liberals-who-didnt-want-yakub-memon-to-be-hanged/ |title=19 tweets by Adarsh Liberals who didn't want Yakub Memon to be hanged |publisher=Reshareit.com |date=2015-07-30 |accessdate=2015-08-09}}</ref>
