{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2015}}
'''Daniel Monteiro''', a 71-year-old man, was found dead on 30 July 2015 in [[Païta]], [[New Caledonia]]. He was reported missing two days earlier, and his vehicle and credit card had apparently been stolen.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://nouvellecaledonie.la1ere.fr/2015/07/30/le-corps-sans-vie-retrouve-paita-est-celui-de-daniel-monteiro-274545.html|title=Le corps sans vie retrouvé à Païta est celui de Daniel Monteiro|language=French|date=30 July 2015|accessdate=8 August 2015|agency=Nouvelle Calédonie 1ère}}</ref> Prosecutors said he had been "savagely" beaten in a "wild way" to the point of unconsciousness, and then thrown into the Karikaté River, where he drowned. Two men were taken into custody in connection with the theft of his vehicle.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://nouvellecaledonie.la1ere.fr/2015/08/01/daniel-monteiro-ete-battu-de-maniere-sauvage-extremement-violente-274789.html|title=Daniel Monteiro a été battu "de manière sauvage, extrêmement violente"|language=French|date=1 August 2015|accessdate=8 August 2015|agency=Nouvelle Calédonie 1ère}}</ref> A 21-year-old woman confessed to Monteiro's slaying on 3 August 2015, according to French chief prosecutor [[Claire Lanet]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://nouvellecaledonie.la1ere.fr/2015/08/03/une-troisieme-personne-interpellee-dans-l-affaire-du-meurtre-de-daniel-monteiro-275501.html|title=Une jeune femme écrouée dans l'affaire du meurtre de Daniel Monteiro|language=French|date=3 August 2015|accessdate=8 August 2015|agency=Nouvelle Calédonie 1ère}}</ref>

The death of Monteiro was notable for igniting a silent protest by more than 3,000 people, who walked through the streets of [[Nouméa]] on 8 August in a demonstration against recent violence in New Caledonia. The protest was led by Jennifer Seagoe, president of the Chamber of Commerce, who presented a white paper proposing reforms to curb violent crime to French High Commissioner [[Vincent Bouvier]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.radionz.co.nz/international/pacific-news/280838/concern-at-violent-attacks-stirs-mass-rally-in-new-caledonia|title=Concern at violent attacks stirs mass rally in New Caledonia|date=8 August 2015|accessdate=8 August 2015|agency=Radio New Zealand}}</ref>

