{{italic title}} {{Use British English|date=April 2018}} {{Infobox musical |name=Miss Littlewood |image=Miss_Littlewood_artwork.jpg |caption= |music=Sam Kenyon |lyrics=Sam Kenyon |book=Sam Kenyon |basis=The life of [[Joan Littlewood]] |productions={{ubl|2018 [[Stratford-upon-Avon]]<!--Please add only major-market productions in the box. Other professional productions can be described in the Productions section below.-->}} |premiere_location=[[Swan Theatre, Stratford-upon-Avon]]|premiere=3 July 2018|premiere_date={{Start date|df=yes|2018|7|3}}}}
'''''Miss Littlewood''''' is a [[Musical theatre|stage musical]] with music, lyrics and book by Sam Kenyon.
It is based on the life of theatre director [[Joan Littlewood]] and the formation of the [[Theatre Workshop]] which found residency at [[Theatre Royal Stratford East]].
== Production == The musical is produced by the [[Royal Shakespeare Company]] and made its world premiere at the [[Swan Theatre, Stratford-upon-Avon|Swan Theatre]] in [[Stratford-upon-Avon]] on 3 July 2018 (with previews from 22 June) for a limited 6 week run until 4 August.
The production is directed by [[Erica Whyman]] with design by [[Tom Piper]], lighting design by Charles Balfor, musical supervision and orchestrated by [[Sarah Travis]], musical direction by Tarek Merchant, sound by Jonathan Ruddick and movement by Lucy Hind. The musical has been developed in collaboration with [[Theatre Royal Stratford East]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.whatsonstage.com/stratford-upon-avon-theatre/news/exclusive-clare-burt-joan-littlewood-rsc-musical_46291.html|title=Exclusive: Clare Burt to star as Joan Littlewood in RSC's new musical this summer|access-date=2018-04-18|language=en-GB}}</ref>
The full cast was announced on 13 April 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thestage.co.uk/news/2018/clare-burt-make-rsc-debut-joan-littlewood-musical/|title=Clare Burt to make RSC debut in Joan Littlewood musical|date=2018-04-13|work=The Stage|access-date=2018-07-04|language=en-US}}</ref>
The playtext was published by Samuel French Limited on 21 June 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.samuelfrench.co.uk/s/64297/miss-littlewood?variantId=107506|title=|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref> A cast recording, produced by Gareth Cousins, was recorded at the Swan Theatre during the musical's preview period and will be released from the RSC shop and iTunes from 1 August 2018 featuring 13 tracks.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://shop.rsc.org.uk/collections/miss-littlewood/products/miss-littlewood-cd-2018|title=Miss Littlewood: CD (2018)|website=The RSC shop|access-date=2018-07-24}}</ref>
